  "text": "(iii) The third example is Tetrahymena which contains three very similar tRNA Gln isoacceptors. Two of them with the anticodons UUA and CUA are cytosol-specific and recognize the stop codon UCA which has been reassigned to glutamine in the nucleus of Tetrahymena. The third tRNA Gln with the anticodon UUG recognizes the standard glutamine codons and is in part imported into mitochondria [CITATION_1] . In an in vivo analysis, it was shown that the anticodon UUG of the imported tRNA Gln is both necessary and sufficient to induce import of any of the three tRNA Gln molecules [CITATION_2] . However, no protein interacting with the import signal has been identified yet.",
